aws_cloudfront_public_key.description: Provides a CloudFront Public Key which you add to CloudFront to use with features like field-level encryption.

comment.description: An optional comment about the public key.

encoded_key.description: The encoded public key that you want to add to CloudFront to use with features like field-level encryption.

name.description: The name for the public key. By default generated by Terraform.

name_prefix.description: The name for the public key. Conflicts with `name`.

caller_reference.description: Internal value used by CloudFront to allow future updates to the public key configuration.

etag.description: The current version of the public key. For example: `E2QWRUHAPOMQZL`.

id.description: The identifier for the public key. For example: `K3D5EWEUDCCXON`.
